n/363736107405337970/";s:6:"domain";s:16:"fi.pinterest.com";}}s:9:"sentences";a:72:{i:0;s:110:"Chair yoga is a general term for practices that modify yoga poses so they can be done while seated in a chair.";i:1;s:179:"These modifications make yoga accessible to people who cannot stand lack the mobility to move easily from standing to seated to supine positions or want a quick break from office.";i:2;s:76:"Many of the basic body mechanics of the individual postures remain the same.";i:3;s:19:"See alsoChair Pose.";i:4;s:39:"Adjust Utkatasana for Better Alignment.";i:5;s:98:"About Our Pro Teacher and model Robyn Capobianco MA E-RYT 500 is a corrective-exercise specialist.";i:6;s:97:"Her classes are a unique blend of self-myofascial release classical yoga and corrective exercise.";i:7;s:113:"Exhale and flex your spine drawing your navel to your spine and moving your shoulder blades away from each other.";i:8;s:66:"Sync movement and breath as you perform a few rounds of this pose.";i:9;s:128:"Seated Forward Bend Uttanasana Sitting in a chair for long period of time can compress your spine particularly the lumbar spine.";i:10;s:79:"Chair pose is a standing yoga posture that strengthens the core and lower body.";i:11;s:112:"In this pose the arms extend upward alongside the ears while the knees bend as if sitting on an imaginary chair.";i:12;s:60:"This is an important pose in yoga for energizing the entire.";i:13;s:79:"In Sun Salutation B sequence chair pose is the second pose after mountain pose.";i:14;s:139:"In Light on Yoga BKS Iyengar shows in Chair pose thighs ideally should be parallel to the floor and torso slightly bends to open the chest.";i:15;s:57:"In Bikram Yoga its practiced known as awkward chair pose.";i:16;s:20:"This ones a win-win.";i:17;s:62:"Build confidence and get a full-body stretch at the same time.";i:18;s:34:"Sit tall at the edge of your seat.";i:19;s:116:"Bend your right knee to the side and stretch your left leg out behind you as you press down through your outer heel.";i:20;s:37:"Hold for five breaths then repeat on.";i:21;s:24:"Seated chair yoga poses.";i:22;s:154:"Begin each posture seated on a chair with your spine long and straight both feet flat on the floor letting your hands rest on top of your knees or thighs.";i:23;s:23:"Mountain pose Tadasana.";i:24;s:93:"Take a deep breath and on an exhale root your bodyweight into the chair using your sit bones.";i:25;s:80:"The Chair Pose in yoga also helps in the stimulation of the heart and diaphragm.";i:26;s:105:"Performing this pose is actually quite easy unlike other poses that seem easy but end up being difficult.";i:27;s:93:"The Chair Pose not only helps with stamina but also helps you perform all the standing poses.";i:28;s:50:"Yoga Poses Meditations Sequences and Free Classes.";i:29;s:172:"Apart from Chair Pose or Utkatasana there are other names also known as fierce pose dangerous pose lightning bolt pose wild pose or Bikram yoga weird pose Awkward Pose etc.";i:30;s:86:"These asanas are quite easy to see but when you do it you may find it a bit difficult.";i:31;s:144:"Practice the chair yoga posture that effectively reduces the symptoms of flat feet and pain caused in the ankles legs and hips due to flat feet.";i:32;s:77:"Utkatasana is a cost-effective and safe alternative to surgery for flat feet.";i:33;s:89:"The everyday practice of chair pose effectively reduces stress and tranquilizes the mind.";i:34;s:26:"8 Chair Yoga Poses to Try.";i:35;s:88:"Fuller believes it is good to build a little heat in the body to warm up for chair yoga.";i:36;s:82:"She suggests doing a few arm circles forwards and back to get your shoulders warm.";i:37;s:76:"Then do a few leg swings while standing if you are able hold onto the chair.";i:38;s:109:"Each month we feature a new yoga pose in hopes of inspiring you to practice the yoga pose with your children.";i:39;s:107:"Check out the collection of pictures below where children from around the world demonstrate the focus pose.";i:40;s:36:"This months challenge is Chair Pose.";i:41;s:171:"Chair pose or Utkatasana may be a pose that strengthens the shoulders hips glutes and back while simultaneously stretching the Achilles tendon and the shoulders and chest.";i:42;s:91:"Its also believed to assist stimulate the muscles and organs in your abdomen including the.";i:43;s:33:"Yoga Poses Chair Pose Utkatasana.";i:44;s:105:"In Tadasana or Mountain pose firmly root into the ground finding equal weight on all corners of the feet.";i:45;s:76:"Inhale to bring the arms up overhead moving the upper arm-bones up and back.";i:46;s:63:"Turn the palms to face each other or place the palms in prayer.";i:47;s:54:"Exhale to bend the knees as though sitting in a chair.";i:48;s:114:"Chair pose strengthens the feet ankles knees thighs glutes back and shoulders and can help to alleviate knee pain.";i:49;s:133:"Yoga 15 with Abi Carver is a series of 15-minute yoga videos designed to enhance your athletic performance and support your recovery.";i:50;s:42:"Help me to start a movement in your sport.";i:51;s:19:"What is Chair Pose.";i:52;s:104:"Chair pose or utkatasana is a powerful standing yoga asana that requires balance stability and strength.";i:53;s:88:"The arms extend upward alongside the ears while the knees bend as if sitting on a chair.";i:54;s:51:"Begin in mountain pose with your big toes touching.";i:55;s:113:"Chair Pose or Utkatasana in Sanskrit is a standing yoga posture that tones the entire body particularly the legs.";i:56;s:174:"The Sanskrit name comes from the words utkata meaning powerful or fierce and asana meaning pose and make no mistake Chair Pose can be a fierce posture for your thigh muscles.";i:57;s:48:"Here are The Best Chair Yoga Poses and Benefits.";i:58;s:60:"To practice yoga on the chair you must start with breathing.";i:59;s:65:"Sit up straight on your chair and place your hands on your belly.";i:60;s:39:"Now relax yourself and start breathing.";i:61;s:39:"Try to push your breath into your core.";i:62;s:75:"Does this pose daily as this will provide you with strength and resistance.";i:63;s:74:"Chair yoga involves modifying yoga poses so they can be done while seated.";i:64;s:75:"With the support of a chair the benefits of yoga become accessible to even.";i:65;s:50:"Lower Back Abdominals Thighs Glute Muscles Ankles.";i:66;s:21:"Chair Pose yoga pose.";i:67;s:21:"Ask Yogi Maharaj- Dr.";i:68;s:42:"Twitter 56K Followers ORDER YOGA MAGAZINE.";i:69;s:72:"Chair yoga is a gentle form of yoga you can do while sitting on a chair.";i:70;s:68:"You can also do some poses while standing using a chair for support.";i:71;s:95:"It is great for people who have limited mobility or if you want to practice yoga while at work.";}}